Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees. Remove the outer leaves from the @cauliflower{1/2}. Separate the cauliflower into florets. Cut the top and bottom off the @courgette{1}, cut in half lengthways and then cut lengthways again so you have four strips. Chop each strip into three pieces.

Put your cauliflower and courgette onto a #baking tray{} and sprinkle over the @nigella seeds{1%tsp} and half of the @ground turmeric{1/2%tsp}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and drizzle over some @oil{}. Mix well to make sure your veggies are nicely coated with the spices and oil. Pop in your oven and roast for ~{25%minutes}.

> The cauliflower should be slightly browned and crispy when ready.

While your veggies cook, cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and then chop into small cubes. Peel and chop the @garlic clove{1}.

Heat a #saucepan{} over medium heat and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Add your onion and cook for ~{3%minutes}, add your garlic, your remaining turmeric and the @mustard seeds{1%tsp} and cook for another ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @basmati rice{175%g}, give it a stir to make sure it is nicely coated with the turmeric, then pour in the @water{350%ml} (as specified in the ingredient list). Add the @vegetable stock pot{1} and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium-low and pop on the #lid{}. Cook for ~{10%minutes} and then remove from the heat. Leave the lid on for another ~{10%minutes} for perfectly cooked rice!

Now chop the rest of the ingredients to make a salsa. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}. Chop the @vine tomatoes{2} into 1cm pieces and place in a #bowl{}. Remove the root from the @spring onion{3} and slice as thinly as possible. Add your spring onion to your tomato and mix with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and your coriander. Grate in the zest of the @lime{1} and squeeze in its juice. Remove the shells and chop the @pistachios{25%g}.

When your rice is cooked, carefully mix in the @raisins{1} and half of your pistachios. Serve your roasted veggies on top of a generous amount of rice and then finish the dish with your salsa and a sprinkling of pistachios.